===Etymology===
From {{etyl|frm}} {{term|blond|lang=fr}} {{m}}, from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|blond|blond, blont|lang=fro}}, of {{etyl|gem}} origin, from {{etyl|frk}} {{recons|blund|blund|a mixed color between golden and light-brown|lang=frk}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|blundaz||mixed, blinding|lang=gem-pro}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|bʰlendʰ-||to become turbid, see badly, go blind|lang=ine-pro}}. Compare {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|blondenfeax|''blonden''feax|grey-haired|lang=ang}}, {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|blandan||to mix|lang=ang}}. More at {{l|en|blend}}.

Alternate etymology connects {{etyl|frk|-}} {{recons|blund|lang=frk}} to {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|blundaz||blond|lang=gem-pro}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|bʰl̥ndʰ-|lang=ine-pro}}, {{recons|bʰlendʰ-||blond, red-haired|lang=ine-pro}}. Cognate with {{etyl|sa|-}} {{term|ब्रध्न||tr=bradhná|ruddy, pale red, yellowish|lang=sa}}.

