====Usage notes====
* In English, this is one of a few words which can show gender, with "blond" being used of males and "blonde" of females, following French usage. 
* Some writers, especially in the US treat the spellings as interchangeable or use ''blond'' gender-neutrally.
* Traditional terms for light hair in English are "''fair(-haired)''", "''[[flaxen]]''", and "''[[towhead|tow headed]]''".

